text: Józef Rysula (13 March 1939 - 23 November 2020) was a Polish cross-country skier. He competed at the 1960 Winter Olympics, the 1964 Winter Olympics and the 1968 Winter Olympics. He was born in Kościelisko, Poland. Rysula died on 23 November 2020 at the age of 81. ==References== Category:1939 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Olympians for Poland Category:Polish skiers
